251
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:51,567
do you really like Tonyo?

252
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:53,200
Or are you just targeting Bobby?

253
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:54,567
There's nothing wrong with that.

254
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:55,567
I'm single.

255
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:58,533
And as far as I know,
Tonyo is single too.

256
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,533
But you guys are together
at the station.

257
00:12:01,667 --> 00:12:02,933
That's not an issue.

258
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:04,133
And why?

259
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:07,200
He and Bobby were also an item
at Station 12, right?

260
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:10,733
And if it were an issue,
it would be easy to move.

261
00:12:10,867 --> 00:12:12,433
You really have an answer
for everything, don't you?

262
00:12:12,567 --> 00:12:14,833
You're not used to me yet.

263
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,200
But you know, I'm the one
who's wondering about you.

264
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:20,767
Why do you seem so invested
in my love life?

265
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:22,100
Why? Are you jealous?

266
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,800
- That's mine! My bag...
- Give it to me!

267
00:12:26,933 --> 00:12:28,800
Hey Stop! Stop!

268
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:31,533
Sir! My bag, Sir.

269
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:34,967
Sir, thank you.

270
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,800
- Madam.
- Sir, my bag.

271
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:39,933
Thank you, Sir, Ma'am.

272
00:12:40,067 --> 00:12:41,067
You're surprised, aren't you?

273
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,067
Suddenly, there's a policeman.

274
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,567
You're unlucky, boy.
Come here, let's go!

275
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:45,133
Stand up!

276
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:47,867
Don't move.

277
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,100
What?

278
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:51,167
You still haven't answered
my question.

279
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:53,367
Are you jealous?

280
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,333
I just see you as my sister,
Charlie.

281
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:58,100
So, as your brother,
I want to give you some advice.

282
00:12:58,233 --> 00:13:02,400
All I know is that Tonyo and
Bobby have a deep foundation.

283
00:13:02,533 --> 00:13:04,467
You'll only get hurt if you try
to get in the picture.

284
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:10,067
Captain, since we're done
patrolling,

285
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,767
maybe we can go home?

286
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:13,200
Okay, let's go home.

287
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:14,500
- Okay.
- Thank you!

288
00:13:14,633 --> 00:13:16,700
- Abdul, Marsy, we'll go ahead.
- Take care.

289
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:17,833
Go straight home.

290
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:22,033
What are you waiting for?

291
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,900
Let's go, let's go on patrol.

292
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,167
Captain, we just finished
patrolling.

293
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:29,267
Our guards have asked
for permission to go home.

294
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:31,033
- That's right.
- Did you forget right away?

295
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:33,300
Let's go home!

296
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:34,733
I'm sleepy.

297
00:13:34,867 --> 00:13:36,567
What are you talking about?

298
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:37,867
It's still early.

299
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,000
Come on, let's go on patrol.

300
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:41,567
Let's give it to her.

301
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,033
Captain might be having
an attack.

302
00:13:43,167 --> 00:13:44,333
- Come on.
- Let's go.

303
00:13:50,233 --> 00:13:51,467
It's Ma'am Sophia!

304
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:53,600
And her assistant
with an attitude!

305
00:13:53,733 --> 00:13:55,067
What? You want round two?

306
00:13:55,233 --> 00:13:57,100
- Come on, bring it! What?
- All right!

307
00:13:57,233 --> 00:14:00,000
- What?
- Cheka, stop it.

308
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:01,533
- Sorry, Madam.
- We didn't come here

309
00:14:01,667 --> 00:14:03,767
to taunt others.

310
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:07,033
What's the reason you came here
to us?

311
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:12,033
To talk to you
about your grandchild

312
00:14:12,167 --> 00:14:15,567
who's forcing herself into
our family.

313
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:24,633
Thank you.

314
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:25,333
Thank you, Miss.

315
00:14:25,467 --> 00:14:27,167
We'll pay, later, Miss.

316
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:28,733
Thank you.

317
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:31,433
This is really delicious.

318
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,800
- Delicious?
- This is Boss Tonyo's favorite.

319
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:35,900
I'll try it.

320
00:14:37,067 --> 00:14:38,133
Right?

321
00:14:39,433 --> 00:14:40,667
- Let's go there.
- All right.

322
00:14:41,967 --> 00:14:42,967
This is good.

323
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:45,867
That's their problem, Dude.

324
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,067
The important thing is,
let's go see our friend.

325
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,867
- Hey, Vince!
- Vince! Faye!

326
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:50,900
What are you doing?

327
00:14:51,033 --> 00:14:52,667
Boss Tonyo ordered us
to do something.

328
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:55,033
Okay, go get some fish balls.

329
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:57,300
- Are you sure?
- Hey, there's no problem here.

330
00:14:57,433 --> 00:14:58,767
My treat.
I'll take care of it.

331
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:02,000
Hey, it's Mayor.

332
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:03,000
Glen?

333
00:15:03,133 --> 00:15:04,867
Yes, of course.

334
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:05,967
Mayor!

335
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:08,267
Cecilia.

336
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,433
Hi, Faye!

337
00:15:10,733 --> 00:15:11,733
Faye...

338
00:15:23,267 --> 00:15:24,667
You should know by now

339
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:27,967
that I'm contesting
Joaquin's inheritance

340
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:29,967
to that bastard.

341
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:32,833
Captain, Bobby said,

342
00:15:32,967 --> 00:15:35,833
there's a chance
to withdraw the case.

343
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,867
Well, it's in the Court.

344
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,633
So what else are we going
to talk about?

345
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:47,867
Well, I plan to drag
this case into eternity,

346
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:52,067
so your grandchild
will definitely get nothing,

347
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:55,233
but there's another option.

348
00:15:55,367 --> 00:15:56,233
Cheka.

349
00:15:56,367 --> 00:15:57,333
Madam.

350
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:02,900
Take it.

351
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:09,633
That's five million pesos.

352
00:16:12,267 --> 00:16:13,467
What's in return?

353
00:16:14,667 --> 00:16:17,767
So that Bobby
can forgo her claims.

354
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:22,067
For the peace of mind
of our lives,

355
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:25,633
take it and give it to Bobby.

356
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:27,567
That's more than enough.

357
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:30,733
You can't collect
that much money.

358
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:35,700
You want me to give up
my granddaughter's rights?

359
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:40,433
Don't you understand me?

360
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:45,400
If you fight me,
you won't gain anything.

361
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:05,467
If you will fight me,
you will get nothing.

362
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,533
Well then, nothing.

363
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:12,100
Stick it in your lungs!

364
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,700
My daughter is the one who
committed a sin against you,

365
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:16,500
not my grandchild.

366
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:18,533
So stop bothering Bobby!

367
00:17:18,667 --> 00:17:20,500
I reached out to you

368
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:22,700
because I thought
you'd be more sensible

369
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,600
because of your age,

370
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:29,900
but you and your grandchild
are just as stubborn.

371
00:17:30,033 --> 00:17:33,267
You will regret making
an enemy out of me.

372
00:17:34,767 --> 00:17:35,833
Cheka.

373
00:17:41,033 --> 00:17:43,400
Just in case you change
your mind...

374
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:46,100
call me.

375
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:47,633
Oh my god!

376
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,400
Mar, stop me.

377
00:17:49,533 --> 00:17:51,433
Oh my god.

378
00:18:08,733 --> 00:18:10,000
Who's that again?

379
00:18:11,067 --> 00:18:12,833
Why are you massaging me?

380
00:18:12,967 --> 00:18:14,367
Come on, come on.

381
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:16,633
Let's go, let's go.

382
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:20,167
- Come on! Let's go!
- That's Ma'am Sofia.

383
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:22,967
Cecilia.

384
00:18:24,233 --> 00:18:25,700
Will you go with us now?

385
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:30,333
Faye, that's why you didn't have
someone pick you up,

386
00:18:30,467 --> 00:18:32,400
someone else will.

387
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:36,400
Glen, Vince's friends
are with us.

388
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:37,633
Mayor is so cool, right?

389
00:18:37,767 --> 00:18:39,367
He drives his own car.

390
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:43,033
The Mayor doesn't need
a bodyguard.

391
00:18:43,167 --> 00:18:45,600
But, Mayor, if you need
a bodyguard, we can.

392
00:18:45,733 --> 00:18:46,600
We're cheap!

393
00:18:46,733 --> 00:18:48,333
Okay, thanks for that

394
00:18:48,467 --> 00:18:51,400
but I don't have any enemies
to have a bodyguard.

395
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:54,800
As for the driver,
I can do that.

396
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:56,833
Those are good words
of wisdom, Mayor.

397
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:04,033
Glen, can you settle something
for me and Vince?

398
00:19:04,167 --> 00:19:06,567
Because he feels like
you don't like him.

399
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:09,800
Hey, Faye, that's embarrassing
for your brother.

400
00:19:09,933 --> 00:19:12,067
Mayor, I'm sorry.

401
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,300
No, it's okay.

402
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:16,433
You know, Faye, Vince was very
instrumental in stopping

403
00:19:16,567 --> 00:19:18,867
the sale of drugs
at your school.

404
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,300
What's not to like about him?

405
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:23,800
Hey, hey, hey!
The Mayor likes him! Lucky!

406
00:19:23,933 --> 00:19:26,700
- But...
- Oh no, there's a but.

407
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:29,867
But Faye is too young
to have a boyfriend.

408
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:32,500
Glen, he's not my boyfriend yet.

409
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:34,733
Mayor, we're just friends.

410
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:37,067
Okay, that's good.

411
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:39,333
Faye, let's go.
Say goodbye to your friends.

412
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:41,767
Come home with me.
Let's go.

413
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:44,900
Brother, I haven't paid
for the fish ball yet.

414
00:19:45,033 --> 00:19:46,900
- Yes, of course!
- You promised, Faye.

415
00:19:47,033 --> 00:19:48,267
Fish ball!

416
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,600
- Mayor, let's go eat.
- It's embarrassing!

417
00:19:49,733 --> 00:19:52,033
- Brother, you promised.
- She promised, Dude.

418
00:19:52,167 --> 00:19:53,900
- Come on.
- Let's go.

419
00:19:54,033 --> 00:19:55,467
Mayor, let's go, eat, Mayor.

420
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:56,533
You're so thick faced.

421
00:19:56,667 --> 00:19:58,333
Give us boiling oil.

422
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:02,067
Glen...

423
00:20:02,233 --> 00:20:04,633
I saw how you looked
at that young man.

424
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,233
Don't do it.

425
00:20:07,367 --> 00:20:08,867
What?

426
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,333
I'm not going to do anything.

427
00:20:10,467 --> 00:20:14,200
I'm not going to do anything
to Faye's friend, okay?

428
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:15,500
Don't worry about it.

429
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,133
Bobby, good morning!

430
00:20:37,267 --> 00:20:39,933
Good morning!
You just woke up?

431
00:20:40,067 --> 00:20:41,033
Yeah, usually,

432
00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:44,233
my alarm is the smell
of Captain's breakfast,

433
00:20:44,367 --> 00:20:46,000
the one she always cooks.

434
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:47,833
But what is she cooking now?

435
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:53,567
I think I smell something
strange.

436
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:55,200
My stomach must have been upset.

437
00:20:57,533 --> 00:20:59,367
You know, you animal!

438
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,567
Why?

439
00:21:00,700 --> 00:21:03,200
I thought the breakfast
I smelled was Captain's cooking.

440
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:05,000
What I smelled was some kind
of fried rice.

441
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:07,333
Captain didn't cook breakfast!

442
00:21:07,467 --> 00:21:08,467
What do you mean she didn't?

443
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:10,367
Look.
She didn't prepare food.

444
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:15,667
Maybe she's still asleep.

445
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,633
Wait, I'll check.

446
00:21:20,367 --> 00:21:21,667
Grandmother...

447
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:23,500
I'm hungry.

448
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:24,933
Grandmother...

449
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,367
Grandmother, I'm going in.

450
00:21:32,767 --> 00:21:33,867
Grandmother?

451
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,733
I don't know either.

452
00:21:36,867 --> 00:21:38,133
She's not here.

453
00:21:38,267 --> 00:21:39,367
She went outside.

454
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:41,500
Wait, I'll call Grandmother.

455
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:46,233
She's been gone for a while.

456
00:21:46,367 --> 00:21:47,900
It seems to be coming
from there, wait.

457
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:49,500
- It's in the kitchen.
- Check it.

458
00:21:56,767 --> 00:21:59,733
Bobby, I saw it there,
in the refrigerator.

459
00:21:59,867 --> 00:22:01,333
- In the refrigerator?
- Yes.

460
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:04,567
Where is Grandmother?

461
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:05,967
I'll check outside.

462
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:08,133
- I'll call the village as well.
- No, I'll go.

463
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:24,800
Is that the boyfriend
of Boss's sister?

464
00:22:24,933 --> 00:22:27,133
He's the reason why Monty
was in jail.

465
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:28,667
Someone told me
that you were talking

466
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,167
to Grandmother last night.

467
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:32,567
I tried to talk to her,
but she wouldn't listen.

468
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:33,700
She's missing.

469
00:22:33,833 --> 00:22:35,267
We've been looking for her
for a while now.

470
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:38,100
Are you trying to insinuate
that I had something to do

471
00:22:38,233 --> 00:22:39,700
with your Grandmother's
disappearance?

472
00:22:39,833 --> 00:22:41,333
Don't worry, Sergeant Enriquez.

473
00:22:41,467 --> 00:22:43,067
We'll help you find
your Grandmother.

474
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,933
Lieutenant Conde
and Lieutenant Garcia

475
00:22:45,067 --> 00:22:45,933
are in the building.

476
00:22:46,067 --> 00:22:47,300
They're watching Dante Eusebio.

477
00:22:47,433 --> 00:22:48,600
Hello, Dante?

478
00:22:48,767 --> 00:22:50,233
Did you know that they already
know you here at Station 12?

479
00:22:50,367 --> 00:22:51,300
And at this moment,

480
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:53,133
there might be police officers
watching you.

481
00:22:53,267 --> 00:22:54,633
Bok, why is he walking
towards us?

482
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:55,900
It looks like he's been warned.

483
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:57,367
Get down!
